     =================================================================
                                 EDITORIAL
     =================================================================

     Greetings,

     I'm supprised at the response received to the Editorial of last
     week's issue.  Thank YOU all who responded!

     It shows, there are many more readers than what some make out to
     believe there to be.  Admitted, not everybody or reader replied to
     the request, but that is, as one responder noted, FidoNet Sysop's.
     However, I'm sure that given time, a few more responses will arrive.

     What is happening?  No word from the new Z1C or is there no ZC for
     Zone 1?  Even the IC makes no comment.

     There is so much talk about what is going to be done, but nothing,
     zilch is done about nothing.  What does this mean to the average
     SysOp?  Do what you think is best for you and your users, if you
     have any left on your BBS.   It's a sad state of affairs, believe
     me.  Sad, in that people WANT to communicate, but the *C's are
     taking the attitude, that if it ain't broke, why fix it.
     Give it some thought and I'll be happy to hear from you all!

     Happy reading,

